<font color="purple" size=+1>
<b>STATEMENT</b></font><br>

<b>All ALTS</b> are accepted into the guild regardless of level<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Exception: Members on probation may not add an alt until the probation period is over
<br><br>

<b>Adding an ALT to the Guild</b><br>
To add an alt to the guild, you must log on your MAIN and request the addition in GUILD CHAT online.<br>
Ask if an IC member is in your area.  Reminder, an IC member may not be in your area or may be busy at the moment, 
please be patient, if this is the case, and re-request it at a later time.<br><br>

<b>Alts in other Guilds Statement</b><br>
The main issue with alts is loyalty and we try to induct people with that attribute. <br>
The fact that some may want to encourage removing alts  from LoM and putting them in other guilds indicates their interests are not 
focused on the family of LoM and we allow it only by special approval only by <b>IC vote</b>.<br><br>





<b><font color="00AAFF">ALTs IN OTHER GUILDS</font></b><br><br>
<li><b>Officers</b> in any position may not have alts in other guilds.  This is a loyalty issue.  If you are an officer in LoM, 
you are expected to have 100% loyalty to the guild.<br><br>
<li><b>Alts ALREADY</b> in LoM. If your alt is already tagged LoM, you may not drop LoM for one of your 
characters without dropping all of your characters.<br><br>

<li><b>MAIN in LoM, ALT never tagged LoM</b>. If your alt was never tagged LoM, you may join your ALT to any guild you please. 
As a whole, we feel this is a messed up loyalty thing, but we cannot force anyone to join their alts.<br>
Mains in this situation may not server as officers on any council.<br><br>

<li><b>DROPPING MAIN from LoM</b>.  All ALTS need to be dropped too.  <br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Exception: By approval of the <u>IC vote</u><br><br>



